<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="initial-scale=1">
<title>doxdox - A simple solution for auto generated documentation.</title>
<meta name="description" content="doxdox is a documentation generator that converts JSDoc comment blocks into easy to read Bootstrap and Markdown documentation files.">
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>

<body>

<header class="page-header">

    <nav class="header-nav">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#getting-started">Getting Started</a></li>
            <li><a href="/neogeek/doxdox">Documentation</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://discuss.doxdox.org/">Forum</a></li>
            <li><a href="#plugins">Plugins</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/neogeek/doxdox">View on GitHub</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="promo">

        <div class="copy">

            <div class="inner">

                <h1 class="logo">doxdox</h1>

                <blockquote class="tagline">A simple solution for auto generated documentation.</blockquote>

                <p><b>doxdox</b> is a documentation generator that converts JSDoc comment blocks into easy to read Bootstrap and Markdown documentation files.</p>

                <div class="actions">
                    <a href="#getting-started" class="btn">Get Started Now</a>
                    <a href="https://github.com/neogeek/doxdox" class="btn">View on GitHub</a>
                </div>

            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="screenshots">
            <div class="inner">
                <img srcset="/images/screenshot-paas-2x.png, /images/screenshot-paas.png 500w" src="/images/screenshot-paas.png">
                <img srcset="/images/screenshot-dash-2x.png, /images/screenshot-dash.png 500w" src="/images/screenshot-dash.png">
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

</header>

<main class="page-content">

    <section id="intro">

        <div class="step">

            <h3>Convert JSDoc comment blocks ...</h3>

            <div class="highlight jsdoc-example-code"><pre><span class="pl-c"><span class="pl-c">/**</span></span>
<span class="pl-c"> * Parse array of directory globs and/or files, and then render the parsed data through the defined layout plugin.</span>
<span class="pl-c"> *</span>
<span class="pl-c"> *     parseInputs(['src/*.js'], {'ignore': [], 'parser': 'dox', 'layout': 'markdown'}).then(content =&gt; {});</span>
<span class="pl-c"> *</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@param</span> <span class="pl-en">{Array}</span> <span class="pl-smi">inputs</span> Array of directory globs and/or files.</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@param</span> <span class="pl-en">{Object}</span> <span class="pl-smi">config</span> Configuration object.</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@param</span> <span class="pl-en">{String}</span> <span class="pl-smi">config.ignore</span> Array of paths to ignore.</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@param</span> <span class="pl-en">{String}</span> <span class="pl-smi">config.parser</span> String representing the parser to be used.</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@param</span> <span class="pl-en">{String}</span> <span class="pl-smi">config.layout</span> String representing the layout plugin to be used.</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@return</span> <span class="pl-en">{Object}</span> Promise</span>
<span class="pl-c"> * <span class="pl-k">@public</span></span>
<span class="pl-c"> <span class="pl-c">*/</span></span></pre></div>

            <script>

            (function () {

                var jsdocExampleCode = document.querySelector('.jsdoc-example-code');

                jsdocExampleCode.addEventListener('click', function () {

                    if (window.getSelection) {

                        var range = document.createRange();
                        range.selectNode(jsdocExampleCode);
                        window.getSelection().addRange(range)

                    }

                });

            }());

            </script>

        </div>

        <div class="step">

            <h3>... into easy to read documentation!</h3>

            <figure>

                <a href="/neogeek/doxdox"><img srcset="/images/screenshot-desktop-2x.jpg, /images/screenshot-desktop.jpg 500w" src="/images/screenshot-desktop.jpg"></a>

                <figcaption>Bootstrap template plugin, included with doxdox</figcaption>

            </figure>

        </div>

    </section>

    <section id="getting-started">

        <h2><span>Getting Started</span></h2>

        <div class="step">

            <h3>Install doxdox with NPM</h3>

            <div class="highlight">
                <pre>$ npm install doxdox -g</pre>
            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="step">

            <h3>Generate documentation</h3>

            <div class="highlight">
                <pre>$ doxdox <span class="pl-s"><span class="pl-pds">'</span>lib/**/*.js<span class="pl-pds">'</span></span> --layout markdown --output DOCUMENTATION.md</pre>
            </div>

            <p class="read-more"><a href="https://github.com/neogeek/doxdox#layouts">Read more about the different layouts available.</a></p>

        </div>

    </section>

    <section id="using-paas">

        <h2><span>Using doxdox.org</span></h2>

        <p>doxdox.org is a hosted, free to use, version of doxdox. It supports GitHub URLs with support for additional hosting services to be added soon.</p>

        <form class="form-documentation-redirect">

            <fieldset>

                <div class="row">
                    <label for="username-and-repo"><span class="https">https</span>://doxdox.org/</label>
                    <input type="text" name="username-and-repo" id="username-and-repo" class="username-and-repo" placeholder="<username>/<repo>" pattern=".+/.+" required>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <button type="submit" class="btn">View Documentation</button>
                </div>

            </fieldset>

        </form>

        <div class="step">

            <h3>Lastest documentation generated</h3>

            <ul class="repo-list">

                {{#each docs}}

                <li><a href="{{url}}">{{username}}/{{repo}}</a></li>

                {{/each}}

            </ul>

        </div>

        <div class="step">

            <h3>Add a badge to your GitHub README.md</h3>

            <p>Specify a GitHub path with the user and repo name to link to dynamically generated documentation.</p>

            <div class="highlight">
                <pre>[![<span class="pl-en">Latest Documentation</span>](https://doxdox.org/images/badge-flat.svg)](https://doxdox.org/&lt;username&gt;/&lt;repo&gt;)</pre>
            </div>

            <p>You can also omit the repo path entirely and doxdox.org will automatically detect what branch it's coming from and redirect you.</p>

            <div class="highlight">
                <pre>[![<span class="pl-en">Latest Documentation</span>](https://doxdox.org/images/badge-flat.svg)](https://doxdox.org/)</pre>
            </div>

        </div>

    </section>

    <script>

    (function () {

        var formDocumentationRedirect = document.querySelector('.form-documentation-redirect');
        var inputUsernameAndRepo = document.querySelector('.username-and-repo');

        formDocumentationRedirect.addEventListener('submit', function (e) {

            e.preventDefault();

            var path = inputUsernameAndRepo.value;

            path = path.replace(/(http(s)?\:\/\/)?(www.)?github\.com\//, '');

            window.location.href = window.location.origin + '/' + path;

        });

    }());

    </script>

    <div class="plugins">

        <section id="plugins">

            <h2><span>Plugins</span></h2>

            <div class="plugin-wrapper">

                {{#each plugins}}

                <div class="plugin">
                    <p>
                        <a href="https://www.npmjs.org/package/{{package.name}}" class="plugin-name">{{package.name}}</a>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <a href="https://www.npmjs.org/package/{{package.name}}"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/{{package.name}}.svg?style=flat" alt="NPM Version"></a>
                        <a href="https://doxdox.org/neogeek/{{package.name}}"><img src="https://doxdox.org/images/badge-flat.svg" alt="Latest Documentation"></a>
                    </p>
                    <p class="plugin-description">{{package.description}}</p>
                </div>

                {{/each}}

            </div>

            <p class="read-more">See more plugins at <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/search?q=doxdox+plugin">npmjs.com</a>.</p>

        </section>

    </div>

</main>

